body.description: Clean, hydrate, soothe and replenish your baby's delicate skin with the 4 in 1 Sensitive Skincare of Huggies Calm Baby Wipes. Each baby wipe is unscented and enriched with oat extract, aloe and vitamin E. Plus, these disposable baby wipes are plant-based* and have been since 1990, so you can feel confident you're giving your baby a gentle clean. To help maintain healthy skin, Huggies Calm wipes are hypoallergenic, dermatologist-tested, pH-balanced and accepted by the National Eczema Association. They are also free of fragrances, parabens, alcohol and dyes, and they do not contain phenoxyethanol or MIT. And with a push button top and EZ Pull 1-Handed Dispensing, it’s easy to grab wipes when your hands are full! Featuring exclusive Disney's Bambi designs that are as cute as your baby, Huggies Calm wipes are the perfect choice to pair with your Huggies diaper! (*70%+ by weight)

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Your skin is extra special and deserves extra care Huggies Calm Wipes do four things at once (kind of like mom) to clean, hydrate, soothe and replenish.
Tough enough for messes, soft enough for your skin You deserve soft, baby, so our Calm wipes are hypoallergenic, dermatologist-tested and pH-balanced.

What makes Huggies Calm Baby Wipes right for you, baby? Sometimes your delicate skin needs extra care, baby. Huggies Calm Baby wipes are plant-based* since 1990 and designed to gently clean while moisturizing your skin. You might be wondering, baby, how do these wipes care for your skin? Our unscented baby wipes are hypoallergenic, dermatologist-tested and pH-balanced. They are also free of fragrances, alcohol, dyes and elemental chlorine. Counting is new to you, baby. So, what does 4-in-1 Sensitive Skincare mean? Our Calm diaper wipes are designed to do four things at once (kind of like mom does!). Made with oat extract, aloe and vitamin E, these baby wipes clean, hydrate, soothe and replenish with every clean. Are these wipes easy to grab one-handed? Mom’s got her hands full, baby. But don’t worry, our wipes have EZ Pull 1-Handed Dispensing so it’s easy to grab just one baby wipe at a time without wasting sheets. Using the toilet is an important lesson to learn, baby, but are Huggies baby wipes flushable? Designed for cushiony softness and durability, Huggies baby wet wipes don’t easily break down after flushing. Please don’t flush baby wipes, and instead use the trash bin for your wipes and diapers.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Love these wipes! Thick and not soaking wet with moisture. They clean really well and I find myself using less of these than other brands like pampers. They are soothing and don’t have any smell at all. My little man has sensitive skin and these are the only wipes I use on him. They are even gentle enough for me to wipe his face and neck without any reaction or bumps.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The perfect wipe!
reviews.reviewText: I have tried so many wipes over the past year in a half and Huggies are definitely my favorite! I have loved the Natural Care line in the refreshing and fragrance free, but I think these new calm wipes have moved into first place! They are nice and thick and have a good amount of moisture to them, but not overly saturated where it leaves my daughters skin wet. Do a great job of cleaning and not smearing anything, if you know you know. These are fragrance free and don't smell chemically how some fragrance-free wipes smell. I also love the updated packaging to the push button pack. The wipes come out even better now! and I of course love the new design to the packaging, SO cute. Huggies will forever be my go-to for diapers and wipes!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best. Wipes. Ever.
reviews.reviewText: I’ve tried a few brands and there are some that fall apart, super fragrant or leave the fuzzies behind on little ones bottom. But this one doesn’t do any of those and is nice and thick. I can pull it out of the package without ripping it and it’s soft for wiping. AND big bonus, it’s recommended by the national eczema association. It’s great for sensitive skin. I can use it on her hands too and not worry she’s eating some nasty scented stuff. Licking your fingers after using a scented wipes is not fun. Trust me. They’re spendy if you buy them in the smaller packages so buy the big box to save some money and trips. Get these they’re awesome

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars If your kid keeps getting diaper rash get these!
reviews.reviewText: Our little one had some extra sensitive skin and would cry every time we changed her. It felt like we were constantly battling diaper rashes. We switched to these wipes and she has not had one rash since! No even a little irritation! We live in a dry climate and I've seen other babies with chapped skin around their mouths in the winter from drooling we use these to clean her cheeks and chin and it's been so good for her skin. Miracle product!
